  "prompt": "Can an L2 visa holder work without EAD?",
  "response": "An L2 visa holder is allowed to work in the United States without needing an Employment Authorization Document (EAD). However, to work legally, they must apply for and receive an EAD after their arrival in the U.S. The EAD allows L2 visa holders to work for any employer. Once they receive the EAD, they can work without restrictions. It's important to ensure that the EAD is valid and that the visa holder complies with all immigration regulations.",
